"Hey, can you refresh my memory on the outcome of the parks budget cut? How many employees weren't rehired, what kind of assistance they received, and what the status of the closed community centers were?"
"I know those centers were expensive and needed significant maintenance and repair. Were they also underutilized?"
"Checking. "

"25 of 50 people still at City. HR helped facilitate placement for staff and offered interview prep help, resume review, career coaching. Sellwood: had significant maintenance needs, didn't meet equity objectives, now under mgmt by SMILE (including preschool/after school). Hillside: no maintenance needs, under mgmt of Lincoln Youth Soccer Association, longtime renters, discussions between them and another nonprofit about providing child development services are underway. Fulton: significant maintenance needs, under mgmt of French immersion school, longtime renters. Decisions were less about utilization than about equity - where services are offered and to whom. "
